name: AarnaRegistry

methods.name: init
methods.desc: Deploy the contract and set the caller as admin.

methods.name: set_validator
methods.desc: Admin assigns a validator address for project reviews.

methods.name: transfer_admin
methods.desc: Admin transfers ownership to a new admin account.

methods.name: ensure_token
methods.desc:
Create the AARNA ASA if it doesn't exist.
Returns the ASA ID.

methods.name: submit_project
methods.desc:
Developer submits a new project for review.
Returns the project index (0-3).

methods.name: approve_project
methods.desc: Validator approves a project and assigns credit amount.

methods.name: issue_credits
methods.desc:
Validator issues AARNA tokens to submitter.
Status: 2 (verified) → 4 (issued). Prevents double-issuance.

methods.name: list_for_sale

args.name: amount
args.desc: number of AARNA tokens to sell

methods.desc:
List AARNA tokens for sale. Uses clawback to escrow tokens
from seller into the contract. Returns the listing index.

methods.name: buy_listing
methods.desc:
Buy tokens from a listing. Buyer sends ALGO payment,
contract transfers escrowed tokens to buyer and forwards ALGO to seller.

methods.name: cancel_listing
methods.desc: Seller cancels their listing. Escrowed tokens returned.

desc:
On-chain registry + marketplace for blue carbon credits.

    Lifecycle: SUBMIT → REVIEW → VERIFY / REJECT → ISSUE → TRADE

    Roles:
      - admin: deploys, creates AARNA ASA, assigns validator
      - validator: approves/rejects, issues credits
      - developer: submits projects
      - any holder: lists/buys credits on marketplace
